&lt;h1&gt;Dental Officer&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full Time&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Permanent&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reference No: J127-A-20-0605&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours: 37.5 hours, 5 days per week (Part Time Considered)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bases: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Meadows Health Centre, 1 Bridgeway Centre, Meadows,&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nottingham, NG2 2JG&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary: Band A - £41,766 - £62,649 pa, pro rata &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Do you want to make a real difference in a socially minded, values driven organisation? &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Do you want to work where your voice can be heard?&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;We are an award winning employee owned social enterprise, providing high quality community dental services across east and central England&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Community Dental Services CIC are looking for clinicians who identify with our values as a Social Enterprise and are passionate about providing care for those most at need.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited from enthusiastic dentists for this post, based in our clinic in at the Meadows Health Centre. Nottinghamshire has a high dental need and is a service providing a wide range of care. Training opportunities will be provided to develop skills and competencies with special care and paediatric patients, such as sedation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will deliver dental treatment and preventative care to patients and clients of Community Dental Services. Nottinghamshire clinics provide dental care for many groups in the community including adults and children patients with additional needs. Peripatetic cover will be required to support clinics across the county including domiciliary care and epidemiological surveys.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Informal discussions welcome, please contact Jane Walker, Operations Manager, jane.walker@cds-cic.co.uk, mobile 07879 486710.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please apply on line at NHS Jobs quoting the above reference number&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date: Friday 6th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview date: Friday 20th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
